I spent too many years of my life being frustrated and unhappy despite hiding it fairly well. Those close to me know this well. Then at the end of 2019-2021 I started fixing it, and in many ways I did! Then not sure why, but in 2022-now I’ve gotten kinda lazy. Maybe because I wanted to just chill and enjoy life for a bit? Idk. 🤷🏻‍♂️ 

I’m usually a go getter and hard worker, but since last year, I’ve been coasting (personal life not work life) and it’s starting to catch up with me. I don’t feel at my best and I’ve let some old bad habits creep up. I’ve let personal goals slip and my my activation energy has been lower than usual. Self sabotage is real. I don’t typically share personal posts like this, but I wanted to remind myself that I’m human, and everyday is a fresh start. There’s a lot of 2023 left to enjoy and live, so cheers to that and happy Tuesday! ♥️

Hello there

#thirsty #monday #bearsofinstagram #bro #huskular

I’ve told most people that know me already but now I’ll more formally break the news! At the end of the month I’ll be moving out of Phoenix and moving into Denver, Colorado!

I’ve been in Arizona for 22 years, and it’s by far, been more than time for me to start a new chapter and adventure. I’m exited to be moving in with my amazing partner Jake @zeroun1v3rse and starting our new lives together. I’ll be renting out my condo in Phoenix (let me know if interested 😉) and starting a new beginning! I’m fortunate that my job is primarily in both Arizona and Colorado so I’ll still be coming back to the Valley for work and to see friends/family. So, it’s more of a see you later than a full on goodbye.

I have so many memories in Phoenix. Great times with friends both still here and those that have also left the city. As I drive around town it gets me a little emotional. From the schools I taught at, the places where I got to play flag football with the amazing PGFFL 🏈, to just plain good times on Melrose or downtown, it’s def an end of an era for me.

Overall I’m excited and can’t wait! I’ll be moving August 28th which also ironically is Jake and my anniversary. If you wanna hangout before I leave just DM me. Cheers to the future! 

#newchapter #denver #moving #bearsofinstagram
Just my thoughts.

As 2023 reaches an end, it’s been a wild but fantastic year! I didn’t tell most people but was laid off in a budget reduction over the holidays last year, however was able to start the this year at a brand new job I am really enjoying. Got a new car in February, got to enjoy some trips between Feb and May and then moved to Denver to be with my phenomenal partner and start a brand new life in August. Found tenants for my condo so I could keep it in November, and now in December I’m just rejoicing in the holiday spirit! I am normally an anxious person, but the cure for anxiety in my experience is gratefulness and I’m so incredibly grateful for everyone and everything in my life. Cheers to 2023 and cannot wait for 2024! 

#2023 #2024 #reflection
